40 SECTION 2.
41 Article 13 of Chapter 1 of Title 7 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
42 licensing of mortgage lenders and mortgage brokers, is amended in Code Section 7-1-1013,
43 relating to prohibition of certain acts, by revising paragraphs (10) and (11) and by adding a
44 new paragraph to read as follows:
45 "(10) Provide an extension of credit or collect a mortgage debt by extortionate means;
46 or
47 (11) Purposely withhold, delete, destroy, or alter information requested by an examiner
48 of the department or make false statements or material misrepresentations to the
49 department or the Nationwide Multistate Licensing System and Registry or in connection
50 with any investigation conducted by the department or another governmental agency; or
51 (12) Engage in unfair or deceptive acts or practices in violation of Code
52 Section 10-1-393.20."
53 SECTION 3.
54 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
55 without such approval.
56 SECTION 4.
57 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
